summary: bts reaction to dating/marrying a muslim girl
title: bts reaction to dating/marrying a muslim girl
body:
➢ requested? yeeee by @beardedmuffingardenflap, I hope you like it love!

••

jin;

jin knew for a while he was ready to settle down and just around that time, you came into his life. your relationship was much uncharted territory for him and many people tried to tell him marrying you wasn’t a good idea because of your different faiths. but Jin’s heart was set on you - and maybe also your mother’s cooking - and he was willing to go on this new path with you one step at a time.

yoongi;

you hadn’t been dating him long before you told him that you were muslim and homeboy was literally like “okay boo, that’s g shit.” haha okay something along the lines of that cause he really won’t mind

he’d find it intriguing to be educated in your religion and to be able to know even more about you but it really wouldn’t change much, once he’s into you, there really is no going back you feel me?

hoseok;

the most loving and adoring fiancé ever I swear. he has everyone in your life in the palm of his hand without even trying and always talks about considering converting just because he wants to be closer to you.

whenever he was curious about something, he would straight up ask because he didn’t want to have a relationship where you didn’t feel like there were things you both couldn’t talk about. in some way, he wanted to be your home away from home.

“so I was thinking, would it be weird for our wedding if we wore like matching hijabs but like we embroidered them with our initials?”

“you make me wonder what really goes on up there.”

namjoon;

he would always remember the day he noticed you in your red hijab that just happened to match your red converse oof

namjoon is a pretty open guy and once he was interested in you, he goes into this whole research in trying to court you the best way he can when he literally could’ve just said hi but whatever

honestly a power couple though? because you both compliment each other well and he loves to spoil you in the best, even when you tell him not to.

he goes to speak with your family privately about proposing to you and just wants it all to go so smoothly and perfect for his perfect lady you get me?

jimin;

when jimin loves someone, he loves them hard and when it came to you he was literally like putty in your hands. protective af even though you’re a strong independent baddie but he knew that many antis around him weren’t speaking well of you just because of your religion and even though he didn’t speak up on criticism about him, he wouldn’t hesitate to say something when it came to you.

“that’s my baby and I love her, what you and your mama gotta say about her is irrelevant.”

taehyung;

he knew you were Muslim even though you weren’t a hijabi but after the proposal and you revealed to him you wanted to start wearing scarves, you’d probably grow to regret it.

every time he went out of the country, he always came back with a whole ass bunch of scarves for you of all different textures and patterns and just spoils the hell out of you. gets all salty when there’s one of his favorites that he hasn’t seen you in.

“I’m telling you! gold is really your color!”

“I don’t wear them for you! and plus you bought me like fifteen gold ones!”

*cue salty ass tae who buys you fifteen more just because*

so respectful of your family and values and wants your families to meet right away because he’s such a family man and begs your mom all the time to make him food and they end up actually really good friends? seriously charms your whole family with ease.

jungkook;

how he found out you were Muslim was when he walked in on you praying once and was shookith for a sec. he waited until you were done then was like,”I’m gonna be honest I thought you were doing yoga at first and I was salty because I thought that was our thing together.”

a whole ass goofball I swear.

jungkook is young and so although he isn’t really thinking about marriage, wanting it to be something he was really ready for, he treated you like an absolute queen. he did have a lot of questions though but sometimes it resulted in him just kind of staring at you cause you bootiful

“is there something on my face?”

“the love of my life”

*cue the cringe*
